Uses of Class
es.upv.i3m.grycap.im.client.ServiceResponse

  • Packages that use ServiceResponse 
    Package Description
    es.upv.i3m.grycap.im.api  
    es.upv.i3m.grycap.im.client  

    • Uses of ServiceResponse in es.upv.i3m.grycap.im.api

      Methods in es.upv.i3m.grycap.im.api that return ServiceResponse 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.addResource(String infId, String radlFile, boolean... context)
      Add the resources specified in the body contents to the infrastructure with ID 'infId'.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.alterVM(String infId, String vmId, String radlFile)
      Change the features of the virtual machine with ID 'vmId' in the infrastructure with with ID 'infId', specified by the RADL document specified in the body contents.
      Return a RADL with information about the virtual machine, like GetVMInfo.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.createInfrastructure(String radlFile)
      Create and configure an infrastructure with the requirements specified in the RADL document of the body contents.
      If success, it is returned the URI of the new infrastructure.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.destroyInfrastructure(String infId)
      Undeploy the virtual machines associated to the infrastructure with ID 'infId'
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.getInfrastructureContMsg(String infId)
      Return the contextualization log associated to the infrastructure with ID 'infId'.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.getInfrastructureInfo(String infId)
      Return a list of URIs referencing the virtual machines associated to the infrastructure with ID 'infId'.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.getInfrastructureList()
      Return a list of URIs referencing the infrastructures associated to the IM user.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.getInfrastructureRADL(String infId)
      Return a string with the original RADL specified to create the infrastructure with ID 'infId'.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.getInfrastructureState(String infId)
      Return a string with the infrastructure state.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.getVMInfo(String infId, String vmId)
      Return information about the virtual machine with ID vmId associated to the infrastructure with ID infId.
      The returned string is in RADL format.
      See more the details of the output in GetVMInfo
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.getVMProperty(String infId, String vmId, String propertyName)
      Return property 'propertyName' from to the virtual machine with ID 'vmId' associated to the infrastructure with ID 'infId'.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.getVMProperty(String infId, String vmId, VmProperties vmProperty)
      Return property 'propertyName' from to the virtual machine with ID 'vmId' associated to the infrastructure with ID 'infId'.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.reconfigure(String infId)
      Perform the reconfigure action in all the virtual machines in the the infrastructure with ID 'infID'.
      This method starts the contextualization process again.
      To reconfigure the VMs see the reconfigure methods that include the 'radl' parameter.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.reconfigure(String infId, String radlFile, int... vmList)
      Perform the reconfigure action in all the virtual machines in the the infrastructure with ID 'infID.' It updates the configuration of the infrastructure as indicated in the 'radlFile'.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.removeResource(String infId, String vmId, boolean... context)
      Undeploy the virtual machine with ID vmId associated to the infrastructure with ID 'infId'.
      The context parameter is optional and is a flag to specify if the contextualization step will be launched just after the VM addition.
      As default the contextualization flag is set to True.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.startInfrastructure(String infId)
      Resume all the virtual machines associated to the infrastructure with ID 'infId', previously stopped with the 'stopInfrastructure' method.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.startVM(String infId, String vmId)
      Perform the 'start' action in the virtual machine with ID 'vmId' associated to the infrastructure with ID 'infId'.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.stopInfrastructure(String infId)
      Stop (but do not undeploy) all the virtual machines associated to the infrastructure with ID 'infId'.
      ServiceResponse InfrastructureManagerApiClient.stopVM(String infId, String vmId)
      Perform the 'stop' action in the virtual machine with ID 'vmId' associated to the infrastructure with ID 'infId'.
